What is JavaScript
Js is a Dynamic computer programming language. It is lightweight and most commonly used as a part os web pages, ehose implementations allow client-side script to intract with the user and make dynamic page, it is an interprated programming language with object oriented capabalities.
client side Js
client side js is the most common from the language the script should be include in or refrenced by an html document for the code to be interpreted by the browser.
it means that a web page need not be static HTML
Advantages of JS
less server intraction = you can validate user input before sending the page off to the server, this saves server trffic, which means less load on your server.

immedicate feedback to the visitors

increased interactivty
Richer interfaces

